---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Return Policy | Jewelry by Johan"
  description="Full return policy, in-store credit terms, cancellation policy, and warranty information for custom meteorite jewelry by Johan."
>
  <Nav />

  <main style="padding-top:68px;">

    <header class="rp-header">
      <div class="rp-bg" aria-hidden="true"><div class="rp-glow"></div></div>
      <div class="container rp-inner">
        <nav class="rp-breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a>
          <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
          <span aria-current="page">Return Policy</span>
        </nav>
        <div class="reveal">
          <p class="label">Policies</p>
          <h1 class="serif rp-heading">Return Policy</h1>
          <p class="rp-sub">
            Our policy reflects the custom, handmade nature of every piece.
            Please read carefully before ordering.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="rp-body section">
      <div class="container-sm">

        <div class="policy-block reveal">
          <h2 class="serif policy-heading">Return Policy</h2>
          <p>
            If you decide to return your purchase for any reason, you must do so within <strong>30 days of receipt</strong>.
            Jewelry by Johan will apply an in-store credit to your account and has the right to use that credit at our
            discretion for your ring. That credit will be used to repair or replace and ship said ring to satisfy our
            guarantee to you the customer.
          </p>
          <p>
            The guarantee is effective for <strong>one (1) year</strong> from the date you receive your ring — this date
            remains the effective date of the guarantee. If you take the ring to any other jeweler to get it resized,
            engraved, or repaired in any way, <strong>the warranty is void</strong>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Returns will be accepted for <strong>IN-STORE CREDIT</strong> as long as the returned merchandise is in normal
            condition based on how long you have had the product. We are not responsible for "Acts of God", misuse, or
            abuse while your purchase is not in our possession.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-divider"></div>

        <div class="policy-block reveal">
          <h2 class="serif policy-heading">In-Store Credit</h2>
          <p>
            We are happy to use the in-store credit towards any item on our website. Please note that in-store credit
            <strong>cannot be used on shipping costs or duties and taxes</strong>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-divider"></div>

        <div class="policy-block reveal">
          <h2 class="serif policy-heading">If You Order the Incorrect Size</h2>
          <p>
            Because of the nature of our unique materials, <strong>our rings cannot be resized</strong>. When we make
            your ring, we create it according to the information you provide. If for any reason the information you
            provide is incorrect, there is a <strong>50% remake fee</strong> based on the current retail cost of the ring.
            Your original ring must be returned to us within 30 days to qualify for these remake fees. If you desire the
            original design to be remade in a different size, you must purchase a custom sizer in that size in order to
            qualify for the remake fee.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our <a href="https://jewelrybyjohan.com/products/ring-sizer-custom-made-1170" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="rp-link">custom ring sizers</a> are
            crafted in the width and size of your desired item and allow for easy and accurate assessment of your size.
            If you purchased a custom ring sizer and it fits, and an item you receive is made in the wrong size, we will
            re-make the item for <strong>no cost</strong> (valid one time).
          </p>
          <p>
            <a href="https://jewelrybyjohan.com/collections/signature-styles" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="rp-link">Signature Styles</a> can
            be exchanged for the correct size (only whole and half sizes available) — simply contact us within thirty days
            to arrange an exchange. If your desired size is not available in stock, our standard production turn-around
            time would apply.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-divider"></div>

        <div class="policy-block reveal">
          <h2 class="serif policy-heading">Engraved Rings</h2>
          <p>
            If there are any defects in your engraving that we are responsible for, it qualifies for our return policy.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-divider"></div>

        <div class="policy-block reveal">
          <h2 class="serif policy-heading">Canceling the Sale</h2>
          <p>
            You may cancel your order within <strong>three business days</strong> after your order confirmation email is
            sent and you will receive a full refund. The only exception to this is if your order was originally processed
            through PayPal. Due to PayPal's 2019 change in its
            <a href="https://www.paypal.com/us/legalhub/useragreement-full" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="rp-link">User Agreement</a> for online
            sellers, any orders originally processed through PayPal that are canceled and/or result in a refund will be
            refunded the amount due minus PayPal's processing fees of <strong>2.9% + $0.30</strong>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Orders canceled after the three-business-day window will be issued a <strong>50% refund in the form of
            in-store credit</strong>. We reserve the right to cancel any sale or order at any time.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="policy-divider"></div>

        <div class="policy-note reveal">
          <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" aria-hidden="true">
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M12 8v4M12 16h.01"/>
          </svg>
          <p>
            Our refund policy reflects the custom, handmade nature of every piece. Have more questions?
            Visit our <a href="https://jewelrybyjohan.com/pages/faqs" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="rp-link">full FAQ page</a> or
            visit our <a href="https://jewelrybyjohan.com/pages/returns" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="rp-link">RGA Requests page</a> to submit a return or service request.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="rp-cta reveal">
          <a href="https://jewelrybyjohan.com/pages/returns" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-primary">
            Submit a Return / Service Request →
          </a>
          <a href="https://jewelrybyjohan.com/pages/faqs" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-outline">
            Read the Full FAQ
          </a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .rp-header {
    position: relative;
    padding: clamp(4rem, 8vw, 7rem) 0 3rem;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .rp-bg { position: absolute; inset: 0; pointer-events: none; }
  .rp-glow {
    position: absolute;
    top: -60px; left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    width: 600px; height: 350px;
    background: radial-gradient(ellipse, rgba(201,144,31,0.08) 0%, transparent 70%);
  }

  .rp-inner { position: relative; max-width: 720px; }

  .rp-breadcrumb {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: .5rem;
    font-size: .8125rem; color: var(--c-text-muted); margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .rp-breadcrumb a { color: var(--c-text-muted); transition: color .2s; }
  .rp-breadcrumb a:hover { color: var(--c-gold); }

  .rp-heading {
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--c-text);
    margin: .5rem 0 1rem;
    letter-spacing: -.02em;
  }

  .rp-sub {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--c-text-muted);
    max-width: 540px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .rp-body { padding-bottom: 6rem; }

  .policy-block {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .policy-heading {
    font-size: clamp(1.3rem, 2.5vw, 1.75rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--c-text);
    margin-bottom: .25rem;
  }

  .policy-block p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--c-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.78;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .policy-block strong { color: var(--c-text); }

  .rp-link {
    color: var(--c-gold);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(201,144,31,0.3);
    transition: color .2s, border-color .2s;
  }
  .rp-link:hover { color: var(--c-gold-light); border-color: var(--c-gold-light); }

  .policy-divider {
    width: 100%;
    height: 1px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--c-border-gold), transparent);
    margin: 2.5rem 0;
  }

  .policy-note {
    display: flex;
    gap: .875rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    background: var(--c-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border-gold);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }

  .policy-note svg { color: var(--c-gold); flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px; }

  .policy-note p {
    font-size: .9375rem;
    color: var(--c-text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .rp-cta {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }
</style>
